CRC: CodeReady Containers
CRC (aka OpenShift Local) is a tool that lets you run a single-node OpenShift cluster on your local machine
without CRC, you need multiple VMs, networking setup, DNS and load balancers etc. with CRC, you need a laptop, a VM and OpenShift. 
$ crc
$ crc setup            
$ crc start
open console: https://console-openshift-console.apps-crc.testing/dashboards
note: if your computer is not powerful enough for CRC, you can use OpenShift sandbox which would be free for 30 days 

once crc setup crc start has been finished, next step would be creating a cluster:
create cluster via one of the cloud platforms, in reality I wouldnt have access to do it since a cluster inlcudes everything like controlplane and worker nodes etc., whereas 
a project in openshift is more like a kubernetes namespace... 

login with redhat account and you can create a cluster in this fleet page: https://console.redhat.com/openshift/overview
after finishing creating the cluster login with developer or kubeadmin account then you'll see the cluster page: https://console-openshift-console.apps-crc.testing/dashboards 
the cluster page shows up a selector with 'developer' and 'administrator' options on top left in the tutorial video, but actually there's no such selector anymore, instead 
it shows label 'core platform' which would be the new UI. 

next step is installing oc: https://console.redhat.com/openshift/downloads

OpenShift Cluster
│
├── Projects
│     ├── Applications
│     ├── Deployments
│     ├── Services
│     ├── Routes
│     ├── ConfigMaps
│     └── Secrets
│
├── Cluster-wide Resources
│     ├── Nodes
│     ├── StorageClasses
│     ├── ClusterRoles
│     └── Operators
│
└── Infrastructure
      ├── Control Plane Nodes
      └── Worker Nodes

there's no more layer between cluster and project, but in enterprise it would commonly be built in this way:

Cluster
│
├── Finance Team
│     ├── finance-dev
│     ├── finance-test
│     └── finance-prod
│
└── Marketing Team
      ├── mkt-dev
      └── mkt-prod

in this case Finance Team and Marketing Team are not a layer, it would be set up through:
user groups
RBAC
naming conventions


